<br>
Solo, there are a few tree spots that have very few adds, and if a wanton (say wan-ton tronera out loud, does it remind you of an old 60-70's song? in spanish maybe?) is up in those slots, its an easy aaxp bonus. The NE most spot, in the corner, between the big rock and the other trees, and the next one to the west next to the creek. The tree by the waterfall also has very few adds, and no the giants won't aggro. In addition the tree in NW corner is also fairly safe.<br>
<br>
Any of these have adds that roam by, but they are fairly rare. Now there is a tree past the 2nd creek (otw to waterfall) on the north wall, that is suicide. Roamers go by there like its a Taco bell in a college town on a saturday night at 3am.<br>
<br>
The scorned can be cleared by a cleric/mage duo (to hope for wanton popslater). Cleric stands next to pet and heals until tree is near Rage (mage has to meter nuking to avoid summoning). At 20h chain stun tree, pull pet off, and nuke hard for finish.<br>
<br>
Even solo if i stand back far enough with FoT, I rarely get cast on by the wantons. <br>
<br>
Great spot, the loot truely sucks ( 20 plus scorned, NOTHING dropped) but the xp is nice until you can get a regular group in PoS or PoV, or if you want to get stuff done around the house. Fwiw toads and giants are the only Kos I've seen in forrest area, and neither seems to wander, safe to go afk while medding back. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zandar>Zandar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 152<br> <font color=#333333>(1/9/03 10:57:03 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm47.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=24.topic&index=29>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.earthlink.net/~zandar01/Jah.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: solo</span><hr size=1> Yeah this has been great advise thanks for sharing it Toyorgrav. It is just nice to be able to solo efficiently again at 65. These things can hardly damage the 61 pet, it is pretty amazing. It is not too difficult to have over 75% mana after the fight and 80% health on the pet. (And I have a small mana pool)<br>
