<br>
I am not in a guild, and I usually can not play for more than 1-2 hours a stretch, so it was always very hard for me to find a group at 62.  I now live in POS, and in all honesty am having some of the most fun I've ever had in EQ.<br>
<br>
I now average 2 AA's a day in 1-2 hour playtime, and I feel like I am actually going somewhere now seeing those AA's start to pile up.  I also make roughly 2k an hour here as well, it's nice to have some money start to collect in my bank.<br>
<br>
How 2k an hour ?, As someone stated earlier the trees drop leaves, bark, and twigs that sell from 45p-90p usually they drop 2-3 at a time when they have some.  Also they drop storm ent sap which is used for POP tradeskills, and on my server (bertoxx) the sap sells like hotcakes at 500p each.  Somedays I'll get 4 or 5 an hour, and other days maybe only 1.  But I still seem to average about 2k an hour here..<br>
<br>
Also I know this thread was about soloing in POS, which I do everyday now <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  But if you know a shammy 60+, the exp is even faster here.  Grab  a shammy and head out the last tunnel to the desert, set up camp along the wall and just pull non stop.  Was getting 4% AA duoed with shammy, and had 0 downtime.  SHammy slows and heals pets, toss in 2 FBOT on the mobs.  We were both always FM at the end of the fight and exp rolled much faster than solo cause we were killing so fast.  By far best exp I've had in awhile.<br>
<br>
Also the mobs in desert, can drop some nice loot.  I got a nice ranged item off a scorpion which I hear sells for 12kish, and also looted a cactus necklace with like +15 to resists off a cactus.  So not a bad cash camp either..<br>
<br>
One more tidbit.  In the desert we pulled and killed every type of mob there was, including the Daiku Raiders.  For fun when we had another mage join us (shammy, 2 mages) I pulled one of the desert giants just to see if we could take them. Well guess what ? 2 mages and a shammy can EASILY take giants !! Yup you heard me right, ended up fight with 80 mana at end too <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
ANyway thanks again to original poster !! <br>
<br>
One happy mage,<br>
